Sixteen women have won the Nobel Peace Prize , fourteen have won the Nobel Prize in Literature , twelve have won the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine , four have won the Nobel Prize in Chemistry , two have won the Nobel Prize in Physics and one , Elinor Ostrom , has won the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences .
Fourteen women have won the Nobel Prize in Literature , more than any other Nobel Prize with the exception of the Nobel Peace Prize .
The first woman to win a Nobel Prize was Marie Curie , who won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1903 with her husband , Pierre Curie , and Henri Becquerel .
